   "source": [
    "import numpy,matplotlib,pandas\n",
    "from general_functions import *\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "font = {'size'   : 14, 'family' : 'serif', 'serif' : 'cm'}\n",
    "plt.rc('font', **font)\n",
    "plt.rcParams['image.interpolation'] = 'nearest'\n",
    "plt.rcParams['lines.linewidth'] = 1\n",
    "plt.rcParams['axes.linewidth'] = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "#Set to true to save pdf versions of figures\n",
    "save_figs = True"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The files used to make the following plots are:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "obj_list = ['HCG16a','HCG16b','HCG16c','HCG16d','NGC848','PGC8210',\n",
    "            'NW_tail','NE_tail','E_clump','S_clump','SE_tail',\n",
    "            'cd_bridge','NGC848S_tail','NGC848S_loop'] \n",
    "#+\".fits\" or +\"_mask.fits\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For each galaxy or feature there is a mini-cube of the HI emission of that object \"name.fits\" and a mask covering all the emission assigned to that objects \"name_mask.fits\". The masks were created manually using the SlicerAstro software (not included in the workflow) and were downloaded along with the raw data from the EUDAT service [B2SHARE](http://b2share.eudat.eu). The exact location of the data are given in the [pipeline.yml](pipeline.yml) file. The mini-cubes were generated in CASA (in the *imaging* step of the workflow), which is described in the script [imaging.py](casa/imaging.py)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Use the mask and mini-cubes to generate a spectrum of each objects and measure the integrated flux, HI mass, mean velocity, and velocity dispersion."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Initialise blank arrays/lists\n",
    "spec = []\n",
    "vel = []\n",
    "flux = numpy.zeros(len(obj_list))\n",
    "mhi = numpy.zeros(len(obj_list)) \n",
    "mean_vel = numpy.zeros(len(obj_list)) \n",
    "vel_disp = numpy.zeros(len(obj_list)) \n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(len(obj_list)):\n",
    "    obj = obj_list[i]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    #Read in the cube and build its axes\n",
    "    cube,cube_ra,cube_dec,cube_vel,bmaj,bmin,pa,beam_factor,cube_dx,cube_dy,cube_dv = read_fitscube(obj+'.fits',True,True)\n",
    "    #Read in the mask\n",
    "    mask,mask_ra,mask_dec,mask_vel = read_fitscube(obj+'_mask.fits')\n",
    "    #Apply the mask to the cube\n",
    "    masked_cube = mask*cube\n",
    "    #Collapse the spatial dimensions of the masked cube to make a spectrum\n",
    "    spec.append(numpy.nansum(numpy.nansum(masked_cube,axis=1),axis=1)/beam_factor)\n",
    "    #Copy the velocity axis\n",
    "    vel.append(cube_vel)\n",
    "    #Calculate the integrated flux\n",
    "    flux[i] = numpy.sum(spec[i]*abs(cube_dv))\n",
    "    #Convert the flux to an HI mass\n",
    "    mhi[i] = numpy.log10(235600.*dist*dist*flux[i])\n",
    "    #Measure the mean velocity\n",
    "    mean_vel[i] = numpy.nansum(spec[i]*cube_vel)/numpy.nansum(spec[i])\n",
    "    #Measure the velocity dispersion\n",
    "    vel_disp[i] = numpy.sqrt(numpy.nansum(numpy.absolute(spec[i])*((cube_vel-mean_vel[i])**2.))/numpy.nansum(spec[i]))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Use the scaling relation of [Jones et al. 2018](www.aanda.org/articles/aa/abs/2018/01/aa31448-17/aa31448-17.html) to predict the expected HI mass of each galaxy based on it's B-band luminosity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Build empty arrays and fill with NaNs\n",
    "Bcmag = numpy.zeros(len(obj_list)) + numpy.nan\n",
    "err_Bcmag = numpy.zeros(len(obj_list)) + numpy.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "#B-band magnitude values from AMIGA private database\n",
    "Bcmag[0:6] = [12.91, 13.25, 13.30, 13.67, 13.37, 15.17]\n",
    "err_Bcmag[0:6] = [0.12,0.13,0.05,0.05,0.10,0.44]\n",
    "\n",
    "#Make HI deficiency estimates\n",
    "pred_mhi,err_pred_mhi = logMHI_pred(numpy.array(Bcmag),dist,numpy.array(err_Bcmag),err_dist)\n",
    "hi_def = pred_mhi - mhi"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Compile all the information calculated above to build a pandas data frame and generate a table equivalent to Table 2 of the paper."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Make pandas dataframe from dictionary\n",
    "hi_data = {'Object': obj_list,\n",
    "           'Flux [Jy km/s]': numpy.round(flux,2),\n",
    "           'Mean Vel. [km/s]': numpy.round(mean_vel,0),\n",
    "           'Vel. Disp. [km/s]': numpy.round(vel_disp,0),\n",
    "           'log MHI [Msol]': numpy.round(mhi,2),\n",
    "           'HI Def.': numpy.round(hi_def,2),\n",
    "           'HI Def. Error': numpy.round(err_pred_mhi,2)}\n",
    "\n",
    "hi_data = pandas.DataFrame(hi_data)\n",
    "hi_data = hi_data.set_index('Object')\n",
    "\n",
    "hi_data[['Flux [Jy km/s]','Mean Vel. [km/s]','Vel. Disp. [km/s]','log MHI [Msol]','HI Def.','HI Def. Error']]"
    "hi_data[['Flux [Jy km/s]','Mean Vel. [km/s]','Vel. Disp. [km/s]','log MHI [Msol]','HI Def.','HI Def. Error']].to_csv('Tab2-HCG16_galaxy_HI_props.csv',index=True)"
   ]
  },
